 @graye2799  Did you understand what I was writing? The biggest threat is social problems – when (not if) AI can do all jobs better than humans, what do you think humans are going to do? That's a HUGE problem and it seems no country has done anything to deal with the issue. And that's going to happen within 10–30 years so we should be feeling hurry.

I'm expecting to see lots of social issues because of AI taking care of all the stuff we often spend most of our days.

I see Universal Basic Income (UBI) as the only practical long term solution but politicians haven't yet figured that out in any country.
